                            <comment id="12846272" author="psmith@apache.org" created="Wed, 17 Mar 2010 03:03:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;attached patch that I think should make life a bit quicker for some.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12846298" author="stack" created="Wed, 17 Mar 2010 04:59:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Paul.  That definetly helps.. things run a good bit faster now.  I&apos;ve made you a contributor and have assigned you this issue.  I was a little enthusiastic purging httpclient &amp;#8211; turns out its needed by stargate &amp;#8211; so I put it back.  Otherwise stuff seems to work fine w/o the others.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12846372" author="lars_francke" created="Wed, 17 Mar 2010 10:38:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;SLF4J is needed by Thrift so we can&apos;t exclude it or limit the scope to test.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The build works again but I haven&apos;t yet run the tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12846395" author="lars_francke" created="Wed, 17 Mar 2010 12:06:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I opened a new ticket for this small problem (Lars George and I weren&apos;t sure about this because this is closed already): &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2336&quot; title=&quot;Fix build broken with HBASE-2334&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2336&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2336&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
